is satisfies the precedence requirement because the medical check only occurs after \\\"ask for updates\\\", but it changes the business behavior by skipping the medical check on the conflict path.\",\n  \"Fallback vacuous-compliance strategy: remove \\\"check medical history\\\" from the process, or replace it with a silent/no-op step if the process notation requires a placeholder. This satisfies the precedence requirement because \\\"check medical history\\\" can no longer occur without a prior \\\"ask for updates\\\", but it should only be used if the medical-history check is not required by business or other compliance constraints.\"\n]",
